import java.util.Scanner;
class exp{
    
    public static void main(String args[])   {
char ch='E';
ch = Character.toLowerCase(ch);
if(ch=='a'||ch=='e'||ch=='i'||ch=='o'||ch=='u')
{
System.out.println("given character is vowel");
}
else
{
System.out.println("given character is a consonant"); 
}

    }
}

OUTPUT:
given character is vowel

DETAILED DESCRIPTION:
The program converts the character to lowercase using Character.toLowerCase(ch).
It then checks if the character is a consonant by ensuring it is a letter ('a' to 'z') and not a vowel ('a', 'e', 'i', 'o', 'u').
If the conditions are met, it prints "Given character is a consonant." Otherwise, it prints "Given character is a vowel or non-alphabetic."
